In this theme, you can use &lt;a href="https://twemoji.twitter.com">Twemoji&lt;/a> kit simply writing emoji and then adding this param in the config.toml file.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-toml" data-lang="toml">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">twemoji&lt;/span> = &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">true&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>More info in the theme wiki on Github.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>